Oyo State has recorded its second death from the novel Coronavirus disease. Governor Seyi Makinde made the announcement via a post on Twitter. The governor stated that the victim was one of the three Coronavirus cases confirmed in the state on Saturday. He said, “Sadly, one of the new COVID-19 cases announced passed away. “This brings the number of COVID-19 related deaths in the state to two. So, there are currently eight active cases in Oyo State.”